  "texts": [
    "For instance, Onal et al. [61] focused on the fundamentals of text information retrieval, while Mitra et al.",
    "[21] presented a brief review of IR methods that use pretrained embeddings and neural networks.",
    "Closer to our work here, Guo et al. [47] surveyed IR approaches that focus only on ranking models using deep neural networks.",
    "Unlike these approaches, our survey targets IR approaches that utilize pretrained transformer encoders like BERT and its variants while also systematically reviewing the challenges of using BERT-based models for IR.Since 2022, there has been remarkable progress in leveraging Language Models (LMs), encompassing Pretrained Language Models (PLMs) and Large Language Models (LLMs).",
    "PLMs such as BERT [44], RoBERTa [141], and GPT [10] undergo pretraining on extensive textual corpora to assimilate worldly knowledge."
  ],
